<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="53" type="distinction from other species">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="53">Distinction from other species.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="53">
This new species can be distinguished from any other 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" genus="Dorstenia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dorstenia" order="Rosales" pageId="4" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">Dorstenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by its fernlike habit, hanging from vertical rock faces and the absence of latex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="53">
The new species is added to the existing key of 
<bibRefCitation author="Berg, CC" journalOrPublisher="The genus Dorstenia (Moraceae) Ilicifolia" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" pagination="1 - 211" refId="B2" refString="Berg, CC, Hijman, MEE, 1999. . The genus Dorstenia (Moraceae) Ilicifolia 2: 1 - 211" volume="2" year="1999">Berg and Hijman (1999)</bibRefCitation>
the &quot;key to succulent and semi-succulent species of the Old World&quot;
</paragraph>
