<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="53" type="phenology">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="53">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="53">The specimens were collected in late October.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="53" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="53">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="53">
<taxonomicName authorityName="M. E. Leal" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" genus="Dorstenia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dorstenia luamensis" order="Rosales" pageId="4" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="luamensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">Dorstenia luamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
M.E.Leal inhabits moist and shady vertical rock faces close to small waterfalls in forest within a riverine forest-open woodland-savanna mosaic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="53" type="distribution and conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="53">Distribution and conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="53">The species is distributed in small populations within the type locality, and according to these demographic characteristics it merits the conservation status of endangered (EN).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="53" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="53">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="53">
The epithet 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">luamensis</emphasis>
refers the Luama Wildlife Reserve which is drained by the Luama River.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
